  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C" class="c1">Well since it appears Verant nerfed/changed the AC spawn in SRo I don't see any reason not to reveal the 'trick'. During the 2 weeks before the last patch we killed him 4 or 5 times and popped him at least 10 (we did all the work and he always seemed to pop in front of anyone else in the zone heh). To do this efficiently you needed tracking otherwise you risk missing a spawn, so if you were camping the AC for hours and hours - I feel for you, I've been there. Anyway, average time this method took to pop the AC was 30-40 minutes, longest was just over an hour, shortest 15 minutes.<br>
<br>
Here is the OLD PH list for the AC (to my knowledge either the PHs have been removed and the AC set to a longer timer or there are new PHs).<br>
<br>
- a jackal (only 1 jackal spawns on the sand area)<br>
- a madman (only one of its kind)<br>
- a sand mummy (only one of its kind)<br>
- Terrorantula<br>
- Hussam<br>
- Ancient Cyclops<br>
<br>
The 3 common PHs would spawn 6 minutes after each other, when it was time for a named spawn nothing would pop after the 6 minutes (newest spawn on tracking goes to the top, so if a PH doesn't show up at the top a named is coming soon). The 3 named spawns were on a timer, so instead of zone pop (6 minutes) they wait a random amount of time before they pop - so if nothing showed up after you killed your last common PH, one of those 3 are coming (10-30 min roughly).<br>
<br>
This was the method to pop the AC before the last patch, since then I have yet to see any of the common PHs wandering around in SRo, so I'm certain they have changed it. We've seen the AC pop twice since the last patch but have no idea how it works now.<br><br></td></tr>
